{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"Hmm, is using THREE.Clock a common thing on node.js? What's your use case?\nMaybe a solution would be to add a polyfill for your project?\n","created_at":"2016-02-12T08:08:45.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/8112#issuecomment-183223354","id":183223354,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/8112","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE4MzIyMzM1NA==","updated_at":"2016-02-12T08:08:45.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/183223354","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"For me, not working on iOS8 based devices. I have added this r73 polyfill and works again:\n\n```\n\/\/\n\nif ( self.performance === undefined ) {\n\n    self.performance = {};\n\n}\n\nif ( self.performance.now === undefined ) {\n\n    ( function () {\n\n        var start = Date.now();\n\n        self.performance.now = function () {\n\n            return Date.now() - start;\n\n        }\n\n    } )();\n\n}\n```\n","created_at":"2016-02-22T12:49:21.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/8112#issuecomment-187157378","id":187157378,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/8112","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE4NzE1NzM3OA==","updated_at":"2016-02-22T12:49:21.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/187157378","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arturitu\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arturitu\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/5744112?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arturitu","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arturitu\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/arturitu","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arturitu\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU3NDQxMTI=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arturitu\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arturitu\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arturitu\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"arturitu","type":"User","id":5744112,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arturitu\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/arturitu\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"@rethink-rlinsalata As you can see [here](http:\/\/caniuse.com\/#search=performance), the High Resolution Time API is widely supported in all major browsers. So it's of course comprehensible to remove the respective polyfill.\n\nI would use in a node.js environment not a polyfill, but the more accurate [process.hrtime()](https:\/\/nodejs.org\/api\/process.html#process_process_hrtime) API. Check out the npm package [present](https:\/\/github.com\/dbkaplun\/present), which is built on top of `process.hrtime`.\n","created_at":"2016-02-28T13:39:40.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/8112#issuecomment-189873527","id":189873527,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/8112","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE4OTg3MzUyNw==","updated_at":"2016-02-28T13:40:02.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/189873527","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"NONE","body":"+1\n\n`THREE.Clock` doesn't work on iOS 8 (Chrome and Safari).\n","created_at":"2016-04-07T18:25:19.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/8112#issuecomment-207037539","id":207037539,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/8112","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIwNzAzNzUzOQ==","updated_at":"2016-04-07T18:25:19.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/207037539","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mwcz\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mwcz\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/364615?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mwcz","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mwcz\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mwcz","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mwcz\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM2NDYxNQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mwcz\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mwcz\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mwcz\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mwcz","type":"User","id":364615,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mwcz\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mwcz\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"The way the values are currently being processed adds up numerical error.\n\nI guess we might as well just use `Date`.\n\n`0.001` is periodic in binary (check the bits [here](http:\/\/babbage.cs.qc.cuny.edu\/IEEE-754\/)). This error can be minimized dividing by `1000`.\n\nFurther, the digits before the dot in `elapsedTime` eat up precision the higher the value gets. I guess the `performance.mark` method might be the intended way to avoid this problem.\n","created_at":"2016-04-07T19:17:47.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/8112#issuecomment-207055449","id":207055449,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/8112","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIwNzA1NTQ0OQ==","updated_at":"2016-04-07T19:25:27.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/207055449","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/3916357?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/tschw","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM5MTYzNTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"tschw","type":"User","id":3916357,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"> I guess the performance.mark method might be the intended way to avoid this problem.\n\nGood suggestion. I just wonder how performant is `performance.mark` and `performance.measure` when we use it in an animation loop. If we want to calculating the elapsed time with `performance.measure`, we always need two marks. The API also recommends to clear obsolet marks and measures which are stored by the browser.\n","created_at":"2016-04-07T19:39:13.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/8112#issuecomment-207060961","id":207060961,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/8112","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIwNzA2MDk2MQ==","updated_at":"2016-04-07T19:40:35.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/207060961","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"@Mugen87 \n\n> I just wonder how performant is performance.mark and performance.measure when we use it in an animation loop.\n\nMaybe we just shouldn't. Milliseconds are actually quite alright when it comes to timing animations. \n\nThe API is for benchmarking, for which we'd have to\n- stop using `random` all over the place, and\n- use a clock that can be switched to provide discrete time (based on a frame counter) for timing the effect\n\nin order to get reproducible results.\n","created_at":"2016-04-07T19:45:21.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/8112#issuecomment-207063104","id":207063104,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/8112","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDIwNzA2MzEwNA==","updated_at":"2016-04-07T19:45:46.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/207063104","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/tschw\/events{\/